### Test Conversation Context Feature
### This file tests the new conversation history feature

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@connectionId = YOUR_CONNECTION_ID
@conversationId = YOUR_CONVERSATION_ID

### 1. First message - Create conversation context
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/process
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "connectionId": "{{connectionId}}",
  "question": "Show me all products",
  "conversationId": null
}

### 2. Follow-up question - Should use context from previous message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/process
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "connectionId": "{{connectionId}}",
  "question": "How many of them are in stock?",
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}"
}

### 3. Another follow-up - Should understand "those" refers to products
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/process
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "connectionId": "{{connectionId}}",
  "question": "What about those with price > 100?",
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}"
}

### 4. Get conversation context to verify history
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/agent/conversation/{{conversationId}}/context
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
